Statement

 Rewrite your pay computation with time-and-a-half for overtime and create a function called computepay which takes two parameters
(hours and rate).
Enter Hours: 45
Enter Rate: 10
Pay: 475.0



Solution

def computency(hours,hourly_rate):


    if int(hours)>40:
          rate=1.5*int(hourly_rate)*(int(hours)-40)
          pay_package=(40*float(hourly_rate))+rate
    else:
        pay_package = int(hours) * float(hourly_rate)
    return pay_package

pay_package=computency(45,10)
print(pay_package)
